tianity and Islam. It unfolds commonalities and differences between the three monotheistic religions as well as the manifold discourses about peace within these three traditions. The book offers fundamental knowledge about the specific understanding of the soul in each one of these traditions, their interdependencies and their relationship to secular world views.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSoulxChristianity. 0aSoulxIslam. 0aSoulxJudaism. 4aDialog. 4aDiskurs. 4aInterreligiosität. 4aSeele.  aDialogue.  aInterreligious discourse.  aSoul.1 aAvery-Peck, Alan J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöttigheimer, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöttigheimer, Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchockenhoff, Eberhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUhde, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel Maximilian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107482770 cprintz978311074818540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783